Philip WEISENTHAL and David Brill, Plaintiffs in Error, v. GREAT WESTERN ELECTRO-CHEMICAL COMPANY, Defendant in Error. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 23, 1926.) No. 319. Joseph Dannenberg, of New York City, for plaintiffs in error. Glenn & Ganter, of New York City (Garrard Glenn and Anson W. H. Taylor, both of New York City, of counsel), for defendant in error.

Before ROGERS, HOUGH, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment (6 F.[2d] 934) affirmed in open court.
